io.reinert.requestor.core.payload

Interface SerializedPayload

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BinarySerializedPayload, CompositeSerializedPayload, InputStreamSerializedPayload, SerializedJsPayload, TextSerializedPayload

    public interface SerializedPayload
    Represents an HTTP payload. It envelops a String.
    Author:
    Danilo Reinert

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static SerializedPayload EMPTY_PAYLOAD

      Returns this serialized payload as a byte array.

      Returns the total length in bytes of this payload if it is known.
      boolean isBytesAvailable()

      • EMPTY_PAYLOAD

        static final SerializedPayload EMPTY_PAYLOAD

    • Method Detail

      • asBytes

        byte[] asBytes()

        Returns this serialized payload as a byte array.

        If the byte array is not available, it automatically converts the string content to bytes.

        Returns:
        The serialized payload as byte[]

      • asString

        String asString()

        Returns this serialized payload as a string.

        If the string is not available, it automatically converts the byte content to string.

        Returns:
        The serialized payload as String

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Tells whether this serialized payload is empty or not.
        Returns:
        true if this serialized payload is empty

      • isStringAvailable

        boolean isStringAvailable()
        Tells whether there's a string content available in this serialized payload or not.
        Returns:
        true if the string representation is already available

      • isBytesAvailable

        boolean isBytesAvailable()
        Tells whether there's a byte content available in this serialized payload or not.
        Returns:
        true if the byte representation is already available

      • getLength

        long getLength()
        Returns the total length in bytes of this payload if it is known. Returns zero otherwise.
        Returns:
        the payload's byte length or zero if it cannot be computable.
